properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 10:16PM CST until January 4 at 12:00AM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Snow Diminishing But Slick Travel Continues...

.The low pressure system that brought a band of moderate to
occasionally heavy snow to portions of north-central and northeast
Iowa this afternoon and evening is finally advancing southward.
As it does so, the snow is gradually diminishing in intensity and
slowly shifting south. Up to one inch of additional accumulation
is possible through midnight. The snow is also starting to
transition to light freezing drizzle on the northern edge of this
departing system, which may result in further slippery travel
conditions in some areas overnight.

Many roads remain snow-covered and slippery. If traveling
overnight, be alert, slow down, and allow extra time to reach
your destination.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow may mix with or change over to
light freezing drizzle, which may result in further slippery
travel conditions in some areas overnight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
